{"type":"message","id":"c5670de9","parentId":"a7dd58e9","timestamp":"2026-02-18T01:54:08.230Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:10a19bb7-7afb-4b24-8478-62555b540c2d daily-ping-telegram] Send the daily ping to Telegram (ID: 1087368827). Fetch: 1) Bitcoin price from CoinGecko API (https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true), 2) Stock prices for NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD using yfinance, 3) Top 5 GitHub repos by stars (https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5). Format as a concise morning summary with emoji and send via message tool to Telegram target 1087368827.\nCurrent time: Wednesday, February 18th, 2026 — 9:54 AM (Asia/Singapore)"}],"timestamp":1771379648227}}
{"type":"message","id":"ca14ec36","parentId":"c5670de9","timestamp":"2026-02-18T01:55:22.763Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":" The user wants me to send a daily ping to Telegram with:\n1. Bitcoin price from CoinGecko API\n2. Stock prices for NVDA, MSFT, GOOGL, INTC, META, AMD using yfinance\n3. Top 5 GitHub repos by stars\n\nLet me fetch this data and send it to Telegram target 1087368827.\n\nI'll need to:\n1. Fetch Bitcoin price from CoinGecko API using web_fetch\n2. Get stock prices using yfinance (I'll need to exec a Python command for this)\n3. Fetch top 5 GitHub repos from the API using web_fetch\n4. Format everything nicely and send via message tool\n\nLet me start by fetching the data in parallel where possible","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" I'll fetch the market data and send your"},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.web_fetch:0","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.coingecko.com/api/v3/simple/price?ids=bitcoin&vs_currencies=usd&include_24hr_change=true"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.web_fetch:1","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://api.github.com/search/repositories?q=stars:>1000&sort=stars&order=desc&per_page=5"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":" functions.exec:2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport yfinance as yf\nimport json\n\ntickers = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nresult = {}\nfor t in tickers:\n    try:\n        stock = yf.Ticker(t)\n        info = stock.fast_info\n        price = info.get('last_price', 'N/A')\n        change = info.get('regular_market_previous_close', 'N/A')\n        if price != 'N/A' and change != 'N/A':\n            pct_change = ((price - change) / change) * 100\n        else:\n            pct_change = 'N/A'\n        result[t] = {'price': price, 'change_pct': pct_change}\n    except Exception as e:\n        result[t] = {'price': 'N/A', 'change_pct': 'N/A'}\nprint(json.dumps(result))\n\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":9415,"output":472,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9887,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771379648230}}
