{"type":"message","id":"a59c0ef1","parentId":"c35497a8","timestamp":"2026-02-18T01:58:49.540Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"   I got stock prices but not the percentage change. That's okay - I have the prices which is the main thing. Let me fetch the previous close data to calculate percentage change.\n\nActually, I can try fetching 2 days of data and calculate the change. Let me try with a 2 day range","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" Let me get percentage change by fetching 2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"   functions.exec:5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport urllib.request\nimport json\n\ntickers = ['NVDA', 'MSFT', 'GOOGL', 'INTC', 'META', 'AMD']\nresults = {}\n\nfor t in tickers:\n    try:\n        url = f'https://query1.finance.yahoo.com/v8/finance/chart/{t}?range=5d&interval=1d'\n        req = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0'})\n        with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=10) as response:\n            data = json.loads(response.read())\n            result = data['chart']['result'][0]\n            closes = result['indicators']['quote'][0]['close']\n            prices = [p for p in closes if p is not None]\n            if len(prices) >= 2:\n                price = prices[-1]\n                prev = prices[-2]\n                change_pct = round(((price - prev) / prev) * 100, 2)\n                results[t] = {'price': round(price, 2), 'change_pct': change_pct}\n            else:\n                results[t] = {'price': round(prices[-1], 2), 'change_pct': 'N/A'}\n    except Exception as e:\n        results[t] = {'price': 'N/A', 'change_pct': 'N/A'}\n\nprint(json.dumps(results))\n\"","timeout":30}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"moonshotai/kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":21162,"output":414,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21576,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stop